	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Programming is much more rules and templates-based than most of things that are considered an art. The same thing could be identically done by many different programmers. This leaves not much place for artistic expression. You can easily change a programmer on a project, end user barely can notice it (only if you change a pro to someone not skilled enough who don't really able to do the job properly). If you change an artist or a musician, it is easier to notice.
<br />
<br />Probably everything could be an art, but some things are more limited in possibilites to be an art than other.
<br />
<br />Also, to have definitive answer we need to have definition of the art itself, and this is not an easy thing by itself.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


